I"4<p>A community is a group of Open Opportunity users who may belong to different agencies, but share a common goal or interest.</p>

<p>You can post an opportunity to a specific community.  When you post to a community, the opportunity will appear on both the community search results and the main Open Opportunities search results. If you donâ€™t select a community, the opportunity will appear to all users.</p>

<p>To post an opportunity to a community:</p>

<ol>
  <li>Sign in to Open Opportunities.</li>
  <li>Click <strong>Create Opportunity</strong> from the main search or landing page.</li>
  <li>Select <strong>Yes</strong> to post the opportunity to a specific community.</li>
  <li>Select the community from the dropdown.</li>
  <li>Follow the remaining steps to create the opportunity and submit.</li>
</ol>
